<br>
Second, I would like to clarify my reason behind the scale. Initially I had planned the raid to obtain a White Dragonscale Cloak. I did not state this on the rules. I then received an offer from a fellow player in advance for the scale, set at 50k. I figured a bard would benefit more from this, and I would also get the cash to buy a cloak. The raid came and went, I got the scale, but was unable to contact my customer. I then found out he had left EQ for DAoC, two days after the raid. To my knowledge his account was canceled. I forgot about it for a while, thinking perhaps he would come back. A month after the raid I decided he was NOT coming back, so I began attempting to sell the scale. Saturday morning 912/20) around 2 AM EST I receive a tell from a rogue Xaell asking how I got the scale. I explained in full that I led the raid, and the rules were pre-established. I was then essentially told I was a &quot;con man&quot; for deceiving my fellow raiders into thinking the scale was randomed. I explained the RBB tradeoff, and he says &quot;What if RBB had not dropped?&quot; Among other what ifs were &quot;What if scale had been the only loot?&quot; &quot;What if only 1 scale had dropped?&quot; I laugh at this. TWO SCALES dropped. End of story. That and the horn went to two very lucky bards (to Ashreyl I apologize). All three bards and the other raiders came with the full knowledge of the rules. When we entered perma i restated them. At the buffhall I restated them again. And again I shouted the rules just before charge. Anyone on the raid who did not know would have had to have been either an idiot or AFK very often and at very innopportune moments.<br>
<br>
I feel no further need to explain myself. I ask you, raiders, to post here explaining that you knew the rules beforehand. I do not feel that anyone was conned, and this whole point should be proven moot.<br>
